# Purpose

Enforce React, Zustand, API layer, routing, form, and styling patterns used in the frontend package. Coding conventions (naming, imports, types, error handling) are in `frontend/coding-standards.mdc`.

# Rules

## Components

- Use functional components only. DO NOT use class components.
- Export components as default exports from their file.
- Types for props live in a co-located `<Component>.types.ts` file.
- Compose from `ui-app/` wrapper components, not directly from `ui/` shadcn primitives.
- DO NOT manually edit files under `src/components/ui/` ‚Äî managed exclusively via `npm run scadd`.
- DO NOT manually edit files in `src/_types/_gen/` ‚Äî managed by `npm run generate-types`.

## State Management (Zustand)

- Store is composed of slices: `createUserSlice`, `createUiSlice`.
- Each slice lives in `store/slices/<name>/`: `<name>.state.ts` (initial state), `<name>.types.ts`, `index.ts`.
- Selectors live in `store/selectors/<name>/`.
- DO NOT call API functions from within store slices.
- Access store state in components via selector hooks: `useUserSelection()`, `useUiSelection()`.
- DO NOT call `useStore.getState()` inside components.

## API Layer

- All HTTP calls go through `api/service/client/rest.ts` (`get`, `post`, `put`, `del`).
- Per-resource functions live in `api/service/resources/<resource>/index.ts`.
- Access token is read from Zustand store inside `rest.ts` and attached as `Authorization: Bearer`.
- `credentials: 'include'` is set on all requests (sends refresh token cookie).
- DO NOT use `fetch` or `axios` directly in components or hooks.
- SSE streams are handled via `@microsoft/fetch-event-source` through `api/service/client/stream.ts`.

## Routing

- Routes are defined in `src/config/` and referenced via `config.routes.*`.
- DO NOT hardcode route strings in components.
- Navigation uses `react-router-dom` v7: `useNavigate`, `useLocation`, `Link`.

## Forms

- Controlled inputs: update a single `state` object with `setState(prev => ({ ...prev, [name]: value }))`.
- Validation schemas use Zod. DO NOT implement custom imperative validation logic.
- Track loading state in component state (`isLoading`), set before the API call, cleared in `finally`.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite`). Utility classes only ‚Äî no inline `style` props.
- `cn()` from `lib/utils` merges classes with `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`.
- Global stylesheets in `src/stylesheets/`.
- `stylelint` enforces CSS rules: `npm run lint-styling`.

# Required Commands

```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev               # Vite dev server (port 5173)
npm run build             # tsc + Vite production build
npm run lint              # ESLint
npm run lint-fix          # ESLint auto-fix
npm run lint-styling      # Stylelint for CSS files
npm run type-check        # tsc --noEmit
npm run generate-types    # Orval: regenerate API types from OpenAPI spec
npm run scadd <component> # Add shadcn component + auto-format
```

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT import from `src/components/ui/` directly ‚Äî use `ui-app/` wrappers.
- DO NOT store access tokens in `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`.
- DO NOT add API calls inside Zustand store slices.
- DO NOT use `fetch` or `axios` directly in components.

# Checklist

- [ ] API calls via `api/service/resources/<resource>` only
- [ ] Zustand state accessed via selector hooks
- [ ] Generated `_gen` types used for API payloads
- [ ] Loading state cleared in `finally` block
- [ ] Tailwind classes merged with `cn()`
- [ ] `npm run lint`, `npm run lint-styling`, `npm run type-check` pass
